  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nova Liniya III</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The new stores would provide the consumer with more efficient distribution channels and greater access to goods at more affordable prices, including access to products which are important for local consumption.  The new stores would also help boost local production of import substituting products in Ukraine.  In addition, the new stores will support local supply chains and create additional jobs.  As four out of the five planned news stores are outside Kyiv, the proposed IFC investment would also support development of retail operations in more underserved markets in Ukraine.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The proposed project (the Project) is a $50 million expansion of the do-it-yourself (DIY) retail chain Nova Liniya (the Company), an existing IFC client. The Project involves the construction of five new DIY stores, one in Kyiv and four throughout regional cities in Ukraine, and will bring the total number of stores operated by the Company to nineteen. The Project will be implemented over two and a half years.</narrative>
  </description>
